"""
Internationalization (i18n) system for the Simple compiler.

This module serves as the main entry point for compiler UI strings and error messages.
It aggregates strings from specialized modules and provides a unified interface for
localization. All user-facing messages in the Simple compiler should be defined here
or in one of the specialized string modules.

@tag:stdlib
@tag:api

Structure:
- strings_common: Parser errors, basic syntax messages (E0001-E0016)
- strings_semantic: Type checking, scoping errors (E1000-E1999)
- strings_advanced: Advanced language features (generics, traits, macros)
- strings_codegen: Code generation and optimization messages (E2000-E2999)
- strings_runtime: Runtime errors and VM messages (E3000+)
- strings_verification: Static analysis and verification messages
- strings_lint: Code style and best practice warnings
- strings_explanations: Detailed error explanations and help text
- strings_extended: Additional diagnostic messages

SDoctest:
```simple
# Import i18n strings for error reporting
use i18n.{SYNTAX_ERROR, UNEXPECTED_TOKEN_MSG, messages}

# Use predefined error titles
val error_title = SYNTAX_ERROR  # "Syntax Error"

# Format error messages with placeholders
val msg = UNEXPECTED_TOKEN_MSG  # "unexpected token: expected {expected}, found {found}"
val formatted = msg.replace("{expected}", "identifier").replace("{found}", "number")
# Result: "unexpected token: expected identifier, found number"

# Look up error codes
val error_message = messages["E1001"]  # Type error message
print error_message  # "Type Error"
```

Localization:
For Korean translations, use `i18n.ko` instead, which imports Korean string modules
(strings_common.ko, strings_semantic.ko, etc.) while sharing the same error code
mappings. The structure mirrors the English version for consistency.
"""

# Import string constant modules - organized by category
use strings_common          # Basic parser and syntax errors
use strings_semantic        # Type system and semantic analysis
use strings_advanced        # Advanced language features
use strings_codegen         # Code generation and optimization
use strings_runtime         # Runtime execution and VM
use strings_verification    # Static analysis and verification
use strings_lint            # Code quality and style warnings
use strings_explanations    # Detailed help and explanations
use strings_extended        # Additional diagnostics

# Import error code mappings (language-independent)
use compiler

# Re-export all string constants from category modules
# These exports make constants available directly via `use i18n.{CONSTANT_NAME}`
export strings_common.*        # E0001-E0016: Parser errors
export strings_semantic.*      # E1000-E1999: Semantic errors
export strings_advanced.*      # Advanced feature messages
export strings_codegen.*       # E2000-E2999: Codegen errors
export strings_runtime.*       # E3000+: Runtime errors
export strings_verification.*  # Verification warnings
export strings_lint.*          # Linter warnings
export strings_explanations.*  # Detailed explanations
export strings_extended.*      # Extended diagnostics

# Re-export error code mappings
# Provides error_code -> message_key lookup table
export compiler.messages       # Dict[text, text] mapping error codes to message constants
